US energy secretary Spencer Abraham says he will recommend that President Bush approve the Yucca Mountain site in Nevada as a permanent underground repository for spent nuclear fuel.<br>
<br>
Mr Abraham announced his long-awaited decision yesterday (Thursday) in an official notification to NevadaÅfs state governor and legislature &amp;#8211; starting the final site approval process. A minimum of 30 days must pass before Mr AbrahamÅfs recommendation can be given to the president.<br>
<br>
